<DocsLayout
  title="Getting Started"
  description="Learn how to get up and running with our documentation platform in just a few minutes."
  headings={headings}
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Welcome to the documentation platform. This guide will help you understand how to get started quickly and efficiently. Whether you're building a new project or integrating with an existing one, we've got you covered.
  </p>

  <blockquote>
    This documentation is designed to be comprehensive yet easy to follow. If you have any questions, don't hesitate to check out our community forums.
  </blockquote>

  <h2 id="prerequisites">Prerequisites</h2>
  <p>Before you begin, make sure you have the following installed on your system:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Node.js</strong> - Version 18.0 or higher</li>
    <li><strong>npm</strong> or <strong>yarn</strong> - Package manager of your choice</li>
    <li><strong>Git</strong> - For version control</li>
  </ul>

  <p>You can verify your Node.js installation by running:</p>
  <pre><code>node --version</code></pre>

  <h2 id="installation">Installation</h2>
  <p>
    There are multiple ways to install and set up your project. Choose the method that works best for your workflow.
  </p>

  <h3 id="using-npm">Using npm</h3>
  <p>The fastest way to get started is using npm:</p>
  <pre><code>npm create my-project
cd my-project
npm install
npm run dev</code></pre>

  <h3 id="using-yarn">Using yarn</h3>
  <p>If you prefer yarn, you can use:</p>
  <pre><code>yarn create my-project
cd my-project
yarn install
yarn dev</code></pre>

